.TH "gpiochip_add_pingroup_range" 9 "gpiochip_add_pingroup_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiochip_add_pingroup_range \- add a range for GPIO <-> pin mapping
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gpiochip_add_pingroup_range
.BI "(struct gpio_chip *gc "  ","
.BI "struct pinctrl_dev *pctldev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int gpio_offset "  ","
.BI "const char *pin_group "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gc" 12
the gpiochip to add the range for
.IP "pctldev" 12
the pin controller to map to
.IP "gpio_offset" 12
the start offset in the current gpio_chip number space
.IP "pin_group" 12
name of the pin group inside the pin controller
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calling this function directly from a DeviceTree-supported
pinctrl driver is DEPRECATED. Please see Section 2.1 of
Documentation/devicetree/bindings/gpio/gpio.txt on how to
bind pinctrl and gpio drivers via the "gpio-ranges" property.
